{"id":"index.html","dependencies":[{"name":"_css_loader","parent":"C:\\Users\\akoch\\my-projects\\accessos\\src\\index.html","resolved":"C:\\Users\\akoch\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\parcel-bundler\\src\\builtins\\css-loader.js"},{"name":"C:\\Users\\akoch\\my-projects\\accessos\\package.json","includedInParent":true,"mtime":1651730196675}],"generated":{"html":"<!doctype html>\r\n<html lang=\"en\">\r\n  <head>\r\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\r\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\r\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io\\accessos\\dist\\custom.18d3a4a7.css\">\r\n    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Mulish\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\r\n\r\n    <title>Accessibility, Equity, and Resources for Crisis Response</title>\r\n  </head>\r\n\r\n  <body>\r\n  \r\n    <!--This is the Nav Bar-->\r\n    <div class=\"container-fluid custombg\" style=\"background-color:#F7F7F7\">\r\n        <!-- Content Here -->\r\n        <nav class=\"navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light fixed-top\" style=\"background-color:#F7F7F7\">\r\n          <div class=\"container-fluid\">\r\n            <a class=\"navbar-brand fw-bold\" href=\"#\">Accessibility, Equity, and Resources for Crisis Response</a>\r\n            <button class=\"navbar-toggler\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#navbarNavDropdown\" aria-controls=\"navbarNavDropdown\" aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Toggle navigation\">\r\n              <span class=\"navbar-toggler-icon\"></span>\r\n            </button>\r\n            <div class=\"collapse navbar-collapse\" id=\"navbarNavDropdown\">\r\n              <ul class=\"navbar-nav\">\r\n                <li class=\"nav-item\">\r\n                  <a class=\"nav-link active\" aria-current=\"page\" href=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/dist/index.html\">Problem</a>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li class=\"nav-item\">\r\n                  <a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/dist/solution.html\">Solution</a>\r\n                </li>\r\n\r\n                <li class=\"nav-item\">\r\n                  <a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/dist/methods.html\">Research</a>\r\n                </li>\r\n\r\n                <li class=\"nav-item\">\r\n                  <a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/dist/design.html\">Design</a>\r\n                </li>\r\n\r\n                <li class=\"nav-item\">\r\n                  <a class=\"nav-link\" href=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/dist/story.html\">Our Story</a>\r\n                </li>\r\n              </ul>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </nav>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!--This is the Header--> \r\n    <div class=\"container-fluid custombg mt-5 mb-5\">\r\n      <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <div class=\"row\">\r\n          <div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/hero-image.png\" class=\"img-fluid float-end\" alt=\"pwa choose emergency\">\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"container-fluid mt-5 mb-5 pt-5 pb-5 \">\r\n      <div class=\"container px-5\">\r\n        <p>Emergency services are not accessible to the deaf and hard of hearing community and they’re not equitable towards people with mental or behavioral health issues.  Traditional 911 emergency services can be particularly dangerous for people at the intersection of these two identities. To address the challenge, our team partnered with accesSOS, a nonprofit organization that aims both to make emergency services accessible to people incapable of calling 911, and to ensure people have alternative options other than 911 for emergency response based on their needs.\r\n          <br>\r\n          <br>\r\n          We set out to learn about the emergency services domain, understand how diverse populations interact with the services, and how we can develop a trusted solution that meets their needs.  Following are some startling findings we uncovered about equity in emergency response in the United States.          <br>\r\n          <br>          \r\n          <br>\r\n        </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!--This is the scrollytelling-->\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"container-fluid\" id=\"root\">\r\n      <div class=\"row justify-content-center\" id=\"scrolly__section\">\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"col-4 scrolly__content\">\r\n\r\n          <div class=\"step\" data-step=\"1\">\r\n            <div class=\"text-block pa-2\">\r\n              <p class=\"text-body-2\"><b>37 Million Americans can't hear or speak out loud.</b></p>\r\n              <p>Despite this, <b>70%</b> of 911 call centers in the US are unable to receive text messages.  The legacy equipment these call centers use is expensive and difficult to replace, and can’t receive text messages or detect location from mobile devices.  This leaves deaf and hard of hearing people with often suboptimal methods for contacting 911 when they are in the throes of an emergency situation.</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"step\" data-step=\"2\">\r\n            <div class=\"text-block pa-2\">\r\n              <p class=\"text-body-2\"><b>1 in 10 Fatal police encounters have involved an individual with a known mental illness.</b></p>\r\n              <p class=\"text-body-2\">Nationally, <b>104 people</b> undergoing a mental health crisis were fatally shot by police in 2021 alone.  In the majority of the country, police have little training to deal with situations involving people with mental illness.</p>\r\n            </div>            \r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"step\" data-step=\"3\">\r\n            <div class=\"text-block pa-2\">\r\n              <p class=\"text-body-2\"><b>7-10% of US police contacts involve persons with mental illnesses, with a disproportionate amount of these encounters resulting in arrest</b></p>\r\n              <p class=\"text-body-2\">Offenses tend to be minor, such as trespassing or disorderly conduct.  An estimated 685,000 people with severe mental illness are incarcerated nationally every year.</p>\r\n            </div>            \r\n          </div>\r\n          <div class=\"step\" data-step=\"4\">\r\n            <div class=\"text-block pa-2\">\r\n              <p class=\"text-body-2\"><b>An estimated 44% of people in jail and 37% of people in prison have a mental health condition.</b></p>\r\n              <p class=\"text-body-2\">And 10 - 25% suffer severe mental health concerns such as schizophrenia.  Correctional facilities have become de-facto mental health institutions, yet often don’t provide the treatment people really need.</p>\r\n            </div>            \r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"col-6 scrolly__chart\">\r\n          <iframe scrolling=\"no\" src=\"https://flo.uri.sh/story/1240000/embed#slide-0\"></iframe>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n \r\n  <script src=\"https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.slim.min.js\" integrity=\"sha384-DfXdz2htPH0lsSSs5nCTpuj/zy4C+OGpamoFVy38MVBnE+IbbVYUew+OrCXaRkfj\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script>\r\n  <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\" integrity=\"sha384-Piv4xVNRyMGpqkS2by6br4gNJ7DXjqk09RmUpJ8jgGtD7zP9yug3goQfGII0yAns\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script>\r\n  <script src=\"https://unpkg.com/d3@5.9.1/dist/d3.min.js\"></script>\r\n  <script src=\"https://unpkg.com/intersection-observer\"></script>\r\n  <script src=\"https://unpkg.com/scrollama\"></script>    \r\n  <script src=\"https://public.flourish.studio/resources/embed.js\"></script>\r\n  \r\n  <script>var scrolly = d3.select(\"#scrolly__section\");\nvar chart = scrolly.select(\".scrolly__chart\");\nvar content = scrolly.select(\".scrolly__content\");\nvar step = content.selectAll(\".step\"); // initialize the scrollama\n\nvar scroller = scrollama(); // generic window resize listener event\n\nfunction handleResize() {\n  // 1. update height of step elements\n  var stepH = Math.floor(window.innerHeight * 1);\n  step.style(\"height\", stepH + \"px\");\n  var figureHeight = window.innerHeight * 0.75;\n  var figureMarginTop = (window.innerHeight - figureHeight) / 2;\n  chart.style(\"height\", figureHeight + \"px\").style(\"top\", figureMarginTop + \"px\"); // 3. tell scrollama to update new element dimensions\n\n  scroller.resize();\n} // scrollama event handlers\n\n\nfunction handleStepEnter(response) {\n  var textblock = step.select(\".text-block\"); // add color to current step only\n\n  textblock.classed(\"is-active\", function (d, i) {\n    return i === response.index;\n  }); // update graphic based on step\n\n  var linkHead = 'https://flo.uri.sh/story/1240000/embed#slide-';\n  var slide = response.index;\n  d3.select('.scrolly__chart iframe').attr('src', linkHead + slide);\n}\n\nfunction setupStickyfill() {\n  d3.selectAll(\".sticky\").each(function () {\n    Stickyfill.add(this);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction init() {\n  setupStickyfill();\n  handleResize();\n  scroller.setup({\n    step: \"#scrolly__section .scrolly__content .step\",\n    offset: 0.7\n  }).onStepEnter(handleStepEnter); // setup resize event\n\n  window.addEventListener(\"resize\", handleResize);\n}\n\ninit();</script>\r\n  \r\n\r\n\r\n  <!--Storyboard preface-->\r\n    <div class=\"container-fluid custombg mt-5 mb-5 pt-5 pb-5 \">\r\n      <div class=\"container px-5\">\r\n        <p>    \r\n          When people think of emergency services in the United States, they think of 911. People call 911 for assistance in the event of a fire, a medical emergency, or a crime. But sometimes, it isn’t possible for someone to verbally interact through a call.  Other times, interaction with 911 really isn’t the right solution for certain types of crises.  accesSOS’ initial design only enabled contacting 911 (medical, fire, and police), but as we dug deeper into the problem space, our perception of the solution evolved.          <br>\r\n          <br>\r\n          People from different cultural and racial backgrounds and with different abilities have different experiences with 911.  Let’s take a moment and explore how experiences may differ based on an individual’s identity.        </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!--Storyboards-->  \r\n    <div class=\"container px-5 pb-5\">\r\n        <div class=\"container px-5 pb-5\">\r\n          <div class=\"row\">\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-1\">\r\n              <!--intentionally blank-->  \r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story2-1.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story2-2.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story2-3.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story2-4.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story2-5.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-1\">\r\n              <!--intentionally blank-->  \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"container px-5 pb-5\">\r\n          <div class=\"row\">\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-1\">\r\n              <!--intentionally blank-->  \r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story1-1.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story1-2.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story1-3.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story1-4.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-2 text-center\">\r\n              <img src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/assets/Story1-5.png\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"temp-storyboard\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"col-md-1\">\r\n              <!--intentionally blank-->  \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  <!--This is our Scope--> \r\n  <div class=\"container-fluid custombg mt-5 mb-5 pt-5 pb-5\">\r\n    <div class=\"container px-5\">\r\n      <p>All of these individuals have different experiences reaching out to or being the subject of a call to 911.  We can’t shape how emergency services act in a situation.  But we can design a system that ensures equal access to contacting emergency services, and that captures information that is more likely to influence a more appropriate response.  With this mission in mind, we began developing our design for a progressive web app for accesSOS.\r\n        <br>\r\n        <br>\r\n        The debate around policing and 911 in the United States is active and robust.  The issues are numerous, particularly in regards to racial inequities and the militarization of police.  As such, we felt it necessary to narrowly focus on specific facets of the problem space. \r\n        <br>\r\n        <br>\r\n        Our research focused on two primary areas: \r\n        <br>\r\n        <ol>\r\n          <li>User needs for a solution that enables them to contact both traditional emergency services (police, medical, fire) and mental crisis services.</li>\r\n          <li>Understanding the current emergency services landscape at both social and infrastructural levels to be able to incorporate an app into the existing system. </li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n        Learn more about our solution by clicking below.\r\n      </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n  <!--This is the button--> \r\n  <div class=\"container-fluid mb-5 text-center\">\r\n    <a href=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/dist/solution.html\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-lg custombtn\" role=\"button\">What's the Solution?</a>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\n\r\n  <!--This is the Footer-->  \r\n  <div class=\"container-fluid custombg\">\r\n    <div class=\"container\">\r\n      <div class=\"row\">\r\n        <div class=\"col-md-4\">   \r\n            <!-- Placeholder -->\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class=\"col-md-4 text-center\">\r\n            <p>University of California, Berkeley, School of Information, MIMS 2022.</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class=\"col-md-4\">   \r\n            <!-- Placeholder -->\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n  <script src=\"https://amanda-kochak.github.io/accessos/dist/index.js\"></script>    \r\n\r\n\r\n  </body>\r\n</html>"},"sourceMaps":null,"error":null,"hash":"a8dd97aa3b10c4edc4efa304dd883ca2","cacheData":{"env":{}}}